AlishaT wrote a review Jun 2019
Yokosuka, Japan4 contributions7 helpful votes
Great location but noisy
Hotel was very clean and was in a great location (right across from the beach). The only complaints we had was that there is a bar across the street that plays very loud music at very late hours of the night. Also there is construction right next to the hotel which makes relaxing or sleeping difficult due to the noise from the beach and construction. When watching TV we could not hear the television over the noise from outside. Also the food was average or not very good. We ordered buffalo wings and got fried chicken wings with mayonnaise mixed with hot dipping sauce. Staff was friendly, rooms are clean, pool was nice, and my children enjoyed the hotel. Breakfast was the only meal we ate that we really enjoyed. Also the bar serves good drinks.
Responded Jul 2, 2019
Xin chào Alishabe82, Warmest greetings from A La Carte Danang Beach Hotel! Firstly I would like to thank you for taking the time to advise us your stay at the hotel and we are happy to learn that you enjoyed your stay with us especially our friendly staff, wonderful location, good drink and delicious breakfast. We are very sorry reading your review about the noise during your stay with us. We certainly empathize regarding the points you mentioned. We will make sure to send your message to all the departments involve so we can improve the better service for you and others in the future. I hope that we will have a chance to welcome you back to A La Carte Da Nang Beach again soon. Sincerely, The hotel management team.
Janet Lee wrote a review Jun 2019
Really terrible stay! Dirty and noisy!
Very dusty room because of renovations! bad for the health! My child was sneezing so badly throughout the stay. Another thing is that we were trying to sleep at night but then there was a club/party next to the hotel blasting really loud music until midnight. Our sleep were badly affected by this and we had to wake up early the next day. Even when the windows were tightly shut, the noise still affected us. Overall experience was not satisfactory.
Responded Jul 3, 2019
